<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 17 at 11:48PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern
Cleveland and southwestern Pottawatomie Counties through 1215 AM
CDT...
At 1148 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Norman to 4 miles southeast of Lexington.
Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Norman, Slaughterville, Lexington, Pink, Tribbey,
Wanette, Etowah, Macomb, southeastern Lake Thunderbird, Bethel Acres,
Little Axe and Trousdale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
